title: 820-01958-A dead
message: This board was cleaned up before I got it and was told there was some water damage on the underside. There looks like there my have been liquid around U7210/U7220/U7230. All 3 coils L7210/L7220/L7230 read on diode model -0.001v. Am I correct in assuming the Cpu is fried? before I spend more time on this board.

title: 820-01958-A dead
message:
Liquid on the CPU power supplies can be letal.
CPU coils have low values as normal.
You should compare in ohm scale with good board.
Even if no short, CPU can be already damaged...

title: 820-01958-A dead
message: The ohms reading is 2ohms compared to 100ohms on another board.
